27/09/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- The army chiefs of the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania's General Pellumb Qazimi, Croatia's Josip Lucic and Macedonia's Miroslav Stojanovski -- reaffirmed their desire for further co-operation and implementation of NATO integration-related defence reforms, at the beginning of their two-day meeting in Ohrid on Monday (26 September). 
The commanders of the armed forces of BiH, Bulgaria and Serbia-Montenegro, as well as senior US and NATO representatives, also are in attendance. 
Participants are exchanging information about the pace of defence reforms in their countries and discussing ways to boost regional security. 
(Makfax, A1 TV - 26/09/05)
